1
00:00:06,875 --> 00:00:08,875
[somber music playing]

2
00:00:12,666 --> 00:00:14,458
[Shuto] <i>The rich get bored easily.</i>

3
00:00:15,625 --> 00:00:18,666
<i>But… if they won't pay as much,</i>
<i>just take on more clients.</i>

4
00:00:20,375 --> 00:00:21,833
<i>I found you one for today.</i>

5
00:00:22,458 --> 00:00:24,083
<i>Take the pill just in case.</i>

6
00:00:24,166 --> 00:00:26,375
<i>I told him he could finish inside you.</i>

7
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:31,000
<i>Shizuku, since you got tattooed,</i>
<i>it's harder to find clients for you.</i>

8
00:00:31,708 --> 00:00:33,541
<i>Even at 10,000 an hour.</i>

9
00:00:35,208 --> 00:00:36,166
<i>You know what?</i>

10
00:00:36,250 --> 00:00:39,125
<i>I'm thinking you should just find</i>
<i>your own customers from now on.</i>

11
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:53,833
Ten thousand yen. I'll do my best.

12
00:00:53,916 --> 00:00:55,625
[dramatic sting]

13
00:00:55,708 --> 00:00:57,541
[music fades]

14
00:00:57,625 --> 00:01:00,708
It's okay, Shuto.
I'll do anything for you.

15
00:01:00,791 --> 00:01:03,708
[theme music playing]

16
00:01:30,625 --> 00:01:32,625
[cell phone rings]

17
00:01:32,708 --> 00:01:34,666
[woman groans]

18
00:01:34,750 --> 00:01:36,750
[cell phone continues ringing]

19
00:01:40,583 --> 00:01:41,833
SHUTO
NO RESPONSE

20
00:01:41,916 --> 00:01:44,333
Answer already, Shuto, you fuck!

21
00:01:44,416 --> 00:01:45,958
What the fuck is he doing?

22
00:01:46,041 --> 00:01:47,416
[grunts, growls]

23
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:51,208
- Answer me!
- It's okay, Mu-chan.

24
00:01:52,125 --> 00:01:53,791
SHIZUKU
MISSED CALL

25
00:01:53,875 --> 00:01:55,125
[Shuto] What a weirdo.

26
00:01:55,208 --> 00:01:57,416
- What the fuck are you doing?
- [dance music playing]

27
00:01:57,500 --> 00:01:59,291
- What's going on, Shuto?
- Hm?

28
00:01:59,375 --> 00:02:00,500
Is that your girlfriend?

29
00:02:01,083 --> 00:02:04,166
[chuckles] No, just a client.
She has a tab of three million,

30
00:02:04,250 --> 00:02:05,541
so I should answer.

31
00:02:05,625 --> 00:02:06,666
[woman] I guess so.

32
00:02:07,416 --> 00:02:09,041
[Shuto] <i>Blowing up my phone is not okay</i>

33
00:02:09,125 --> 00:02:11,166
<i>when I'm with a customer. LOL.</i>

34
00:02:11,958 --> 00:02:12,916
[Mu-chan] What?

35
00:02:13,458 --> 00:02:15,208
What's with the "LOL?"

36
00:02:15,291 --> 00:02:18,583
He's laughing at you now?!
How dare he disrespect you?!

37
00:02:18,666 --> 00:02:21,958
I don't care if it's work!
Don't you dare talk to other girls!

38
00:02:22,041 --> 00:02:24,708
Delete every single one of their numbers!

39
00:02:24,791 --> 00:02:27,125
Or else I'll kill you!

40
00:02:27,208 --> 00:02:30,000
- [screams]
- It's okay.

41
00:02:31,750 --> 00:02:33,958
It's all good. Don't worry.

42
00:02:41,458 --> 00:02:42,375
[Mu-chan sighs]

43
00:02:43,833 --> 00:02:46,125
[Mu-chan] Ugh, I'm so pissed.

44
00:02:47,791 --> 00:02:49,000
I'm going to work.

45
00:02:50,333 --> 00:02:51,708
Stay home, okay?

46
00:02:54,958 --> 00:02:57,416
[door opens, closes]

47
00:03:00,416 --> 00:03:01,375
[inhales shakily]

48
00:03:01,458 --> 00:03:04,666
[Shizuku] <i>I get so anxious</i>
<i>when Mu-chan's not home.</i>

49
00:03:04,750 --> 00:03:06,916
- [breathing deeply]
- [somber music playing]

50
00:03:14,625 --> 00:03:16,833
[Shizuku] <i>I can't relax unless I'm eating.</i>

51
00:03:16,916 --> 00:03:18,708
[music grows tense]

52
00:03:47,625 --> 00:03:49,625
[groans]

53
00:03:50,916 --> 00:03:53,375
I ate too much again.

54
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:58,083
If I get fat, Shuto won't like me anymore.

55
00:03:58,166 --> 00:04:00,166
[vomiting]

56
00:04:05,583 --> 00:04:07,666
[Shizuku] <i>I wish I could die.</i>

57
00:04:08,666 --> 00:04:11,541
<i>I feel lonely all the time.</i>

58
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:17,541
<i>I'm so lonely, I can't stand it.</i>

59
00:04:18,166 --> 00:04:20,166
[breathes heavily]

60
00:04:21,250 --> 00:04:22,583
<i>Somebody</i>

61
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:24,875
<i>help me.</i>

62
00:04:25,625 --> 00:04:27,625
<i>I need…</i>

63
00:04:27,708 --> 00:04:29,708
[dramatic sting]

64
00:04:37,291 --> 00:04:39,208
Mu-chan.

65
00:04:39,291 --> 00:04:40,875
[music increases in tempo]

66
00:04:40,958 --> 00:04:42,333
[slowly] Shizuku.

67
00:04:49,208 --> 00:04:55,750
Let's drink some water
and brush our teeth and go to bed.

68
00:04:58,458 --> 00:04:59,583
Okay.

69
00:04:59,666 --> 00:05:01,666
[dramatic sting]

70
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:03,166
[music fades]

71
00:05:04,458 --> 00:05:05,833
[Kujo] Let's eat.

72
00:05:16,416 --> 00:05:18,500
It's rare for you to order eel for me.

73
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,000
Is it?

74
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:24,625
It's just… I usually see you eating
nothing but junk food.

75
00:05:24,708 --> 00:05:26,666
Nothing but junk food?

76
00:05:27,958 --> 00:05:31,916
Like the takoyaki that claims to be
the best in Japan or Cup O Noodles.

77
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:36,333
Or what you have there.
That weird slab of meat.

78
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,291
In my opinion,
they all taste just as good as eel.

79
00:05:39,375 --> 00:05:40,291
If you say so.

80
00:05:40,791 --> 00:05:43,208
Anyway,
I guess you and Ms. Kameoka are tied now.

81
00:05:44,625 --> 00:05:45,958
Tied? What do you mean?

82
00:05:46,791 --> 00:05:50,791
You won the Momoka Shiraishi case
settling out of court.

83
00:05:50,875 --> 00:05:52,333
Then she won the Shizuku case.

84
00:05:52,416 --> 00:05:54,625
Her parents were awarded damages,

85
00:05:55,166 --> 00:05:56,625
and her video was pulled.

86
00:06:01,541 --> 00:06:02,458
Check it out.

87
00:06:04,750 --> 00:06:05,708
Look.

88
00:06:05,791 --> 00:06:08,500
"Joan of Arc of the legal world
saves Shizuku Pien

89
00:06:08,583 --> 00:06:11,625
and exposes exploitation
in the porn industry."

90
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:18,708
So now that
Mr. Kyogoku's case has been resolved,

91
00:06:19,791 --> 00:06:21,291
you'll cut ties with him, right?

92
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:25,833
I don't know that anything's resolved yet.

93
00:06:25,916 --> 00:06:26,958
[tense music playing]

94
00:06:27,041 --> 00:06:27,875
Huh?

95
00:06:33,625 --> 00:06:35,291
[Shizuku] <i>I'm scared.</i>

96
00:06:35,375 --> 00:06:37,666
<i>Everyone's staring at me.</i>

97
00:06:38,666 --> 00:06:41,083
<i>Mornings are the worst.</i>

98
00:06:41,166 --> 00:06:43,666
<i>All these people going to work or school</i>

99
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:46,250
<i>and I have nowhere to go</i>
<i>and nothing to do.</i>

100
00:06:47,166 --> 00:06:51,500
<i>A worthless person like me</i>
<i>shouldn't be here with them.</i>

101
00:06:51,583 --> 00:06:53,083
[music becomes upbeat]

102
00:06:53,166 --> 00:06:57,916
<i>If I ever hurt someone,</i>
<i>I hope it's myself.</i>

103
00:06:58,875 --> 00:07:03,750
<i>More than anything,</i>
<i>I want money so I can go see Shuto again.</i>

104
00:07:07,583 --> 00:07:09,000
Mr. Ao!

105
00:07:10,208 --> 00:07:12,541
Mr. Ao!
You have to let me do another movie!

106
00:07:12,625 --> 00:07:14,875
Please! Please!

107
00:07:15,375 --> 00:07:16,666
Fuck! Are you kidding?

108
00:07:16,750 --> 00:07:19,583
Do you have any idea
how much goddamn money you cost us?

109
00:07:20,208 --> 00:07:23,416
I'm sorry! I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

110
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:25,583
What the fuck?! Are you crazy?

111
00:07:25,666 --> 00:07:28,333
I'll call the cops
if I see you here again. Get out of here.

112
00:07:30,041 --> 00:07:32,500
I'm sorry! I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

113
00:07:32,583 --> 00:07:34,083
- [phone buzzes]
- What's wrong with you?

114
00:07:34,166 --> 00:07:36,875
I'm sorry! I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

115
00:07:36,958 --> 00:07:37,833
Yeah, hi.

116
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:41,000
Oh, Madoka!

117
00:07:41,083 --> 00:07:43,291
I was waiting for your call. Huh?

118
00:07:43,875 --> 00:07:47,250
What? You're in the next one?
I'm so happy.

119
00:07:47,750 --> 00:07:50,041
Someone like you
should have a proper debut.

120
00:07:50,125 --> 00:07:52,125
[tense undertone builds]

121
00:07:58,458 --> 00:08:00,375
[music builds]

122
00:08:02,458 --> 00:08:04,458
[music fades]

123
00:08:05,791 --> 00:08:07,166
[Kujo] Are you all right?

124
00:08:11,791 --> 00:08:12,916
Yeah, why?

125
00:08:24,291 --> 00:08:26,083
I'm Mr. Kujo. I'm an attorney.

126
00:08:27,416 --> 00:08:29,416
Please get in touch if you ever need to.

127
00:08:39,791 --> 00:08:42,916
Attorney… Kujo…

128
00:08:50,458 --> 00:08:52,875
- Hi, Mom.
- Oh! Hi, Shinji.

129
00:08:52,958 --> 00:08:54,541
I brought some anmitsu.

130
00:08:54,625 --> 00:08:55,791
Anmitsu? [chuckles]

131
00:08:55,875 --> 00:08:56,708
I love it!

132
00:08:57,291 --> 00:08:59,500
- I was just going to make tea. Hm.
- Great.

133
00:08:59,583 --> 00:09:01,375
[birds chirping]

134
00:09:12,916 --> 00:09:15,000
[bell dings]

135
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,000
[water pouring]

136
00:09:31,041 --> 00:09:32,125
Shinji?

137
00:09:32,208 --> 00:09:33,125
Hm?

138
00:09:33,625 --> 00:09:35,666
How's work going? Good?

139
00:09:36,166 --> 00:09:38,500
Oh, it's really busy.

140
00:09:38,583 --> 00:09:40,916
There are only two of us at the office.

141
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:44,416
And Mr. Kujo takes on a lot of cases
and clients who are complicated.

142
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:49,250
This Mr. Kujo you work for…

143
00:09:50,250 --> 00:09:53,041
He's the one they call the crooked lawyer,
isn't he?

144
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:56,083
I saw it on the internet.

145
00:09:59,458 --> 00:10:00,375
Well?

146
00:10:01,916 --> 00:10:05,083
Is it true? Is he really
the kind of person they say he is?

147
00:10:06,083 --> 00:10:09,083
Mmm… Well,
that's what most people seem to believe.

148
00:10:10,791 --> 00:10:13,625
Are you sure it's a good idea
to work for Mr. Kujo, then?

149
00:10:13,708 --> 00:10:14,541
[chuckles]

150
00:10:14,625 --> 00:10:16,916
Hon, you worked so hard
to become a lawyer.

151
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,958
What if you get involved in something bad?

152
00:10:19,041 --> 00:10:21,791
No, I'll be fine. I'm being careful.

153
00:10:22,916 --> 00:10:24,416
Ugh, I'm starving.

154
00:10:27,208 --> 00:10:28,333
Mmm!

155
00:10:28,416 --> 00:10:29,291
[chuckles]

156
00:10:29,375 --> 00:10:30,625
Good to hear.

157
00:10:30,708 --> 00:10:31,666
[Karasuma chuckles]

158
00:10:31,750 --> 00:10:32,750
[sighs]

159
00:10:34,750 --> 00:10:38,125
It must be difficult… being an attorney.

160
00:10:39,916 --> 00:10:43,666
Especially when you have to defend people
who are just awful.

161
00:10:44,541 --> 00:10:46,833
That's what it means
to be a defense lawyer.

162
00:10:46,916 --> 00:10:48,291
For our justice system to work,

163
00:10:48,375 --> 00:10:50,875
someone has to defend
the rights of the accused.

164
00:10:52,250 --> 00:10:56,708
When you save one,
you… bring sorrow to another.

165
00:10:57,625 --> 00:10:59,625
[somber music playing]

166
00:11:01,833 --> 00:11:03,416
How do you think

167
00:11:04,333 --> 00:11:06,291
Mr. Kujo feels about that?

168
00:11:07,583 --> 00:11:10,583
Doing things that make people
call him a crooked lawyer.

169
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:15,416
ESSENTIAL GUIDE LAW CODES FOR BEGINNERS

170
00:11:22,041 --> 00:11:23,416
[Mrs. Karasuma] Shinji,

171
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:25,041
why don't you stay here tonight?

172
00:11:25,541 --> 00:11:28,125
No, it's okay. I have to get up early.

173
00:11:31,416 --> 00:11:33,166
Is that the one your dad gave you?

174
00:11:33,750 --> 00:11:34,750
Mm-hmm.

175
00:11:35,666 --> 00:11:38,458
Dad said it might be too difficult
for a kid my age.

176
00:11:38,958 --> 00:11:42,291
But he still gave it to me and said,
"You should know how the world works."

177
00:11:42,791 --> 00:11:44,000
I thought I'd take it with me.

178
00:11:45,291 --> 00:11:46,291
Sure.

179
00:11:49,666 --> 00:11:52,000
I must've read it a lot, it's so worn out.

180
00:11:54,541 --> 00:11:56,250
I still remember all of it.

181
00:12:02,625 --> 00:12:03,541
Shinji.

182
00:12:06,541 --> 00:12:09,250
Do you resent him? Your dad?

183
00:12:15,291 --> 00:12:16,291
[Karasuma sighs]

184
00:12:16,958 --> 00:12:18,291
I'm not sure.

185
00:12:19,666 --> 00:12:20,916
Your dad…

186
00:12:22,791 --> 00:12:25,083
I think he's proud of who you are.

187
00:12:27,083 --> 00:12:28,791
You've become a lawyer.

188
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:35,541
He always used to say he wanted you to
be someone who could help other people.

189
00:12:36,208 --> 00:12:38,666
That was the life he wanted for you.

190
00:12:39,875 --> 00:12:43,541
Although, I know for you,
it isn't always easy.

191
00:12:51,125 --> 00:12:56,083
Sometimes, I wonder if…
as a lawyer, I'm really helping people.

192
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:05,458
I'm not even sure what that means anymore.

193
00:13:07,416 --> 00:13:08,625
[music fades]

194
00:13:10,208 --> 00:13:12,666
- [man 1] Are we on the right track?
- [man 2] Yep. It's up here.

195
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:14,750
How 'bout 10,000? For two.

196
00:13:15,875 --> 00:13:17,333
Jesus, scary!

197
00:13:17,416 --> 00:13:19,458
[man 2] She's covered in scars.

198
00:13:19,541 --> 00:13:21,125
[man 1] What a freak.

199
00:13:23,333 --> 00:13:25,708
Baby, I told you.
I had to drink again last night.

200
00:13:25,791 --> 00:13:27,458
[Mu-chan] Oh, another girl, right?

201
00:13:27,541 --> 00:13:29,291
- [Shuto] What?
- [Mu-chan] Another girl.

202
00:13:29,375 --> 00:13:31,791
- [Shuto] No, a client.
- [Mu-chan] You always say it's a client.

203
00:13:31,875 --> 00:13:35,000
- [Shuto] You know you're my girl, Mu-chan.
- Yeah, that was good.

204
00:13:35,083 --> 00:13:36,750
[dramatic sting]

205
00:13:37,875 --> 00:13:39,500
[Shuto] You know you're my girl, Mu-chan.

206
00:13:39,583 --> 00:13:40,958
- [Mu-chan squeals]
- [Shuto chuckles]

207
00:13:41,041 --> 00:13:42,791
[Mu-chan] You're such a good actor!

208
00:13:42,875 --> 00:13:45,250
[tense music playing]

209
00:13:52,250 --> 00:13:54,250
[music builds]

210
00:13:58,833 --> 00:13:59,958
[music ends]

211
00:14:00,833 --> 00:14:03,375
I GOT THE 3 MILLION I OWE YOU.
I SAW YOU GO TO A HOTEL WITH A GIRL,

212
00:14:03,458 --> 00:14:06,166
AND IT MADE ME LOSE INTEREST.
LET’S END THIS.

213
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:08,166
COME TO MY PLACE TO GET IT.

214
00:14:18,208 --> 00:14:19,833
Oh…

215
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:22,833
I ate too much food again…

216
00:14:23,875 --> 00:14:25,125
[chilling music playing]

217
00:14:25,208 --> 00:14:26,791
…Shuto.

218
00:14:31,541 --> 00:14:35,708
But at least I don't have to worry
about you hating me anymore.

219
00:14:41,875 --> 00:14:43,666
[slurping]

220
00:14:45,375 --> 00:14:46,583
[phone chimes]

221
00:14:46,666 --> 00:14:48,833
MU-CHAN:
SHIZUKU! HAPPY 20TH BIRTHDAY!

222
00:14:48,916 --> 00:14:51,250
I’LL BUY A CAKE ON MY WAY HOME.

223
00:14:56,958 --> 00:14:58,958
[music fades]

224
00:15:01,458 --> 00:15:04,083
[Shizuku] The plan was… to kill

225
00:15:04,708 --> 00:15:07,333
Shuto first and then myself.

226
00:15:09,291 --> 00:15:11,416
But I couldn't 'cause I was so hungry.

227
00:15:15,375 --> 00:15:18,375
Isn't that funny, Attorney Kujo?

228
00:15:18,958 --> 00:15:19,833
[clicks tongue]

229
00:15:21,041 --> 00:15:22,625
Ms. Shizuku Kasagi,

230
00:15:23,916 --> 00:15:25,791
if we can establish
diminished responsibility

231
00:15:25,875 --> 00:15:29,000
due to the level of control
Shuto Nakatani exerted over you,

232
00:15:29,083 --> 00:15:31,500
it's possible you'll receive
a suspended sentence.

233
00:15:31,583 --> 00:15:33,250
I think it's your best option.

234
00:15:36,083 --> 00:15:38,208
I won't get the death penalty

235
00:15:38,291 --> 00:15:40,125
even though I killed him?

236
00:15:42,125 --> 00:15:44,458
It's okay if I get the death penalty.

237
00:15:45,625 --> 00:15:47,000
I want to die

238
00:15:48,041 --> 00:15:50,708
so I can say sorry to Shuto in hell.

239
00:15:52,916 --> 00:15:54,125
[Kujo sighs]

240
00:15:56,250 --> 00:15:59,000
A book. It's for you to write in.

241
00:16:00,875 --> 00:16:03,500
If you have anything troubling your mind,

242
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:06,208
write it in this notebook, understand?

243
00:16:07,458 --> 00:16:08,875
I'll be back again tomorrow.

244
00:16:13,333 --> 00:16:16,958
[Karasuma] About Ms. Shizuku Kasagi…
The fact that she called the police

245
00:16:17,041 --> 00:16:19,333
should count toward getting her
a suspended sentence.

246
00:16:19,416 --> 00:16:22,875
Or otherwise, our best course is to argue
for the shortest sentence possible.

247
00:16:22,958 --> 00:16:23,791
[Kujo] Yeah…

248
00:16:24,375 --> 00:16:25,750
I don't know.

249
00:16:25,833 --> 00:16:28,125
I think the chances
of her avoiding jail time

250
00:16:28,208 --> 00:16:31,666
are about the same as…
a pig learning to fly.

251
00:16:31,750 --> 00:16:33,083
- As what?
- [mellow music playing]

252
00:16:33,166 --> 00:16:36,041
How can you make a joke
at a time like this?

253
00:16:36,541 --> 00:16:38,541
[Kujo] It wasn't a joke.
It was an analogy.

254
00:16:38,625 --> 00:16:40,583
Well, it was an inappropriate analogy.

255
00:16:40,666 --> 00:16:42,833
Someone died. Show a little respect.

256
00:16:42,916 --> 00:16:47,125
Oh yeah. Mr. Karasuma,
request a psychiatric evaluation.

257
00:16:47,208 --> 00:16:50,458
It's possible that she was either insane
or had diminished capacity.

258
00:16:50,541 --> 00:16:51,708
Sure. All right.

259
00:16:53,083 --> 00:16:54,458
- Yakushimae.
- Yes.

260
00:16:54,541 --> 00:16:58,500
Could you please look into Shizuku's
upbringing and home environment?

261
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,916
I want to do a mitigation evaluation.

262
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:02,625
I agree. It's just…

263
00:17:03,208 --> 00:17:05,208
Is Shizuku going to make it through this?

264
00:17:06,416 --> 00:17:07,958
<i>Will she be okay?</i>

265
00:17:11,083 --> 00:17:13,083
[cries softly]

266
00:17:14,541 --> 00:17:17,916
[Kujo] <i>Well, she did kill someone,</i>
<i>so I don't think she's okay.</i>

267
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:21,250
It's not as if
she just filleted a fish for supper.

268
00:17:21,333 --> 00:17:23,208
- [music ends]
- [Yakushimae] Tsk.

269
00:17:25,458 --> 00:17:26,875
Yakushimae.

270
00:17:27,708 --> 00:17:29,166
Did you actually just tsk me?

271
00:17:29,250 --> 00:17:33,250
Yes. Absolutely.
The way you say everything pisses me off.

272
00:17:33,333 --> 00:17:35,041
[Karasuma] All right,
all right, all right.

273
00:17:35,125 --> 00:17:37,750
- [music resumes]
- So, Mr. Kujo? What are you doing?

274
00:17:40,041 --> 00:17:43,625
I'm going to visit Shizuku every day
and just listen to her.

275
00:17:44,750 --> 00:17:45,916
Every day?

276
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,083
Yeah.

277
00:17:47,166 --> 00:17:48,125
Every day.

278
00:17:49,750 --> 00:17:53,625
This case is too heavy for Shizuku
to be able to bear it alone.

279
00:17:53,708 --> 00:17:57,541
But if I go,
she might make it through each day.

280
00:17:57,625 --> 00:18:00,333
She doesn't have anyone,
and she needs someone to be there

281
00:18:00,416 --> 00:18:03,250
to listen, so hopefully she'll survive
a day at a time.

282
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:06,291
Oh, I get it.

283
00:18:06,958 --> 00:18:08,916
I guess that's all you can do for now.

284
00:18:10,708 --> 00:18:11,916
[phone rings]

285
00:18:15,333 --> 00:18:18,875
Hello. Kujo Law Office. Yes, that's right.

286
00:18:18,958 --> 00:18:19,875
Yes.

287
00:18:20,708 --> 00:18:21,541
Yes.

288
00:18:21,625 --> 00:18:23,041
My name is Karasuma.

289
00:18:24,916 --> 00:18:26,916
[music fades]

290
00:18:31,166 --> 00:18:32,291
Go ahead.

291
00:18:44,541 --> 00:18:45,583
Ms. Kasagi.

292
00:18:46,083 --> 00:18:49,416
Nice to meet you. I'm Mr. Karasuma.
I work at Mr. Kujo's office.

293
00:18:49,916 --> 00:18:52,541
And… Ms. Kameoka insisted on coming

294
00:18:52,625 --> 00:18:53,958
to see you today.

295
00:18:55,375 --> 00:18:57,333
It's good to see you again.

296
00:19:00,291 --> 00:19:01,625
Have you forgotten?

297
00:19:04,583 --> 00:19:07,875
[Tonohata] <i>Shizuku.</i>
<i>This is the attorney that saved you.</i>

298
00:19:08,583 --> 00:19:10,708
<i>Come on, at least say thank you.</i>

299
00:19:10,791 --> 00:19:11,916
[melancholy music playing]

300
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:13,125
Shizuku,

301
00:19:14,333 --> 00:19:17,333
the adult video
those people forced you to appear in

302
00:19:17,416 --> 00:19:19,083
won't ever be sold ever again.

303
00:19:20,833 --> 00:19:24,333
I'm sure this whole incident was
a painful experience for you,

304
00:19:24,416 --> 00:19:26,625
one which you can't wait to forget.

305
00:19:27,916 --> 00:19:31,000
You've got your whole life ahead of you.
And you can do anything.

306
00:19:35,625 --> 00:19:36,750
[chuckles]

307
00:19:36,833 --> 00:19:41,083
You might want to think of this…
as a chance to start over again.

308
00:19:50,333 --> 00:19:51,791
How did this happen?

309
00:19:56,375 --> 00:19:59,541
You were supposed to be able
to start a new life. What happened?

310
00:20:00,958 --> 00:20:02,208
Tell me.

311
00:20:05,666 --> 00:20:07,125
Well, I…

312
00:20:08,666 --> 00:20:09,750
[Kameoka] What is it?

313
00:20:15,291 --> 00:20:16,958
Being a lawyer…

314
00:20:18,250 --> 00:20:21,125
I suppose lawyers must be really smart?

315
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:27,875
I was never smart,
so I never had that choice.

316
00:20:37,500 --> 00:20:39,416
It's not like I wanted this…

317
00:20:41,625 --> 00:20:43,416
any of this, you know.

318
00:20:47,833 --> 00:20:50,833
You and I live in very different worlds.

319
00:20:52,708 --> 00:20:54,916
You could never understand.

320
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:02,208
[music fades]

321
00:21:09,583 --> 00:21:10,666
[Kameoka] Kujo.

322
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:14,500
Hello, Ms. Kameoka.

323
00:21:14,583 --> 00:21:15,625
What is it about you?

324
00:21:15,708 --> 00:21:17,750
[chuckles] What do you mean?

325
00:21:17,833 --> 00:21:20,333
Shizuku Kasagi is what I mean.

326
00:21:20,916 --> 00:21:23,458
She wants you as her lawyer instead of me.
What did you do?

327
00:21:26,041 --> 00:21:28,500
- [indistinct chatter]
- [music plays in background]

328
00:21:28,583 --> 00:21:29,458
[Kameoka sighs]

329
00:21:30,750 --> 00:21:33,250
So, what is it about you, Kujo?

330
00:21:34,083 --> 00:21:36,750
I was chosen by Shizuku to be her lawyer
because, according to her,

331
00:21:36,833 --> 00:21:38,416
I seem like someone who actually listens.

332
00:21:38,500 --> 00:21:41,916
What is that supposed to mean?
That I don't seem like I listen?

333
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:44,166
See? There it is.

334
00:21:48,958 --> 00:21:49,916
[Kameoka sighs]

335
00:21:50,625 --> 00:21:52,791
You know,
you might try and show some emotion

336
00:21:52,875 --> 00:21:54,625
every now and then, Ms. Kameoka.

337
00:21:55,500 --> 00:21:56,791
You think too rationally,

338
00:21:56,875 --> 00:22:00,125
and that can keep you from truly seeing
people right in front of you.

339
00:22:00,208 --> 00:22:03,958
Everything you say,
the way you say it, gets on my nerves.

340
00:22:04,041 --> 00:22:06,583
I have zero interest
in being lectured to by the likes of you,

341
00:22:06,666 --> 00:22:09,083
a man with no concept of right and wrong.

342
00:22:10,583 --> 00:22:12,291
Excuse me. Here's your grilled crab.

343
00:22:12,375 --> 00:22:13,208
Thank you very much.

344
00:22:15,625 --> 00:22:16,833
[Kameoka] Okay.

345
00:22:17,708 --> 00:22:20,333
Why do you have such a vendetta
against the sex industry?

346
00:22:20,416 --> 00:22:22,916
- Not just me, Japanese law… Careful.
- [Kujo] Oh, you're right.

347
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:25,041
…is almost abolitionist
toward the sex industry.

348
00:22:25,125 --> 00:22:30,166
You're an admirer of the American lawyer
Catherine MacKinnon, aren't you?

349
00:22:30,250 --> 00:22:31,625
[Kameoka] Well, yes.

350
00:22:31,708 --> 00:22:33,708
Are you convinced that
cisgender heterosexual women

351
00:22:33,791 --> 00:22:35,250
are the most exploited group

352
00:22:35,333 --> 00:22:40,125
and that all human society is
fundamentally, as a whole, male-centered?

353
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:44,208
I'm not so rigid
in my thinking on the subject.

354
00:22:45,250 --> 00:22:46,875
My reasoning's more personal.

355
00:22:49,583 --> 00:22:51,666
You don't know this,
but I have a twin sister.

356
00:22:51,750 --> 00:22:52,916
Reiko!

357
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:54,208
[mellow music playing]

358
00:22:54,291 --> 00:22:56,416
[Kameoka] <i>She was always</i>
<i>the complete opposite of me.</i>

359
00:22:57,083 --> 00:22:58,416
<i>She didn't study at all,</i>

360
00:22:58,500 --> 00:23:01,916
and she slept around with
other students and senpais in town.

361
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:03,708
Really anyone she felt like.

362
00:23:04,416 --> 00:23:06,833
<i>We have the same face,</i>
<i>so people in our small town</i>

363
00:23:06,916 --> 00:23:08,458
<i>often mistook me for her.</i>

364
00:23:08,541 --> 00:23:11,208
[boy 1] Hey, let's go
to the mall bathroom again.

365
00:23:11,291 --> 00:23:13,458
[boy 2 chuckles] Pop his cherry this time.

366
00:23:13,541 --> 00:23:14,500
[boy 1] <i>Come on.</i>

367
00:23:14,583 --> 00:23:17,333
[Kameoka] <i>I knew all too well</i>
<i>how men treated my sister.</i>

368
00:23:18,166 --> 00:23:19,208
[gasps]

369
00:23:19,791 --> 00:23:20,708
Stupid whore!

370
00:23:25,375 --> 00:23:28,166
She started going on dates
in exchange for money.

371
00:23:28,833 --> 00:23:32,041
When she was 16,
she got pregnant from one of those guys.

372
00:23:33,083 --> 00:23:36,208
She hid it from our parents,
but they found out by the fifth month.

373
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:39,291
It was too late for an abortion.

374
00:23:41,708 --> 00:23:43,833
She put her daughter in a facility.

375
00:23:43,916 --> 00:23:47,583
She went through several more
pregnancies and abortions.

376
00:23:49,833 --> 00:23:52,000
<i>She still lives back in our hometown.</i>

377
00:23:52,625 --> 00:23:56,750
<i>Barely works,</i>
<i>replacing one man after another.</i>

378
00:24:01,333 --> 00:24:04,416
That's why I became a lawyer.
It was for her.

379
00:24:05,458 --> 00:24:08,083
Because the law isn't fair
to women the way it is.

380
00:24:10,208 --> 00:24:15,375
Fixing that inequality…
will protect my dignity.

381
00:24:16,166 --> 00:24:17,291
That's what I think.

382
00:24:20,125 --> 00:24:21,833
Anyway, it's the only thing I can do.

383
00:24:25,666 --> 00:24:26,916
So, Kujo…

384
00:24:27,416 --> 00:24:29,375
How about we get hammered?
What do you say?

385
00:24:29,458 --> 00:24:30,333
[Kujo] Okay.

386
00:24:33,166 --> 00:24:37,000
- Ladies, do you mind if we say hi?
- You're both very beautiful.

387
00:24:37,083 --> 00:24:39,958
Hey! Don't go flaunting your IDs at them!

388
00:24:40,041 --> 00:24:43,500
Nobody cares what your job is!
I'm sure there's more to you than that!

389
00:24:43,583 --> 00:24:45,375
- Dig deeper!
- [Kujo] I'm sorry. Don't mind her.

390
00:24:45,458 --> 00:24:47,708
- I'm ready for another one, thanks.
- [waitress 1] Coming.

391
00:24:47,791 --> 00:24:49,541
- [waitress 2] You too, sir?
- Yes, please.

392
00:24:54,041 --> 00:24:55,458
[Kujo] It's already morning.

393
00:24:57,916 --> 00:25:00,083
That was the first time I've told anyone.

394
00:25:01,333 --> 00:25:02,458
Hm?

395
00:25:02,541 --> 00:25:04,708
That I have a twin sister.

396
00:25:05,958 --> 00:25:07,208
Is that so?

397
00:25:09,833 --> 00:25:11,916
What is it about you?

398
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:14,333
Well, now, I've got my answer.

399
00:25:17,416 --> 00:25:18,625
Kujo…

400
00:25:19,916 --> 00:25:22,916
You're the only one
who can save Shizuku Kasagi.

401
00:25:25,750 --> 00:25:27,208
She's in your hands.

402
00:25:31,666 --> 00:25:33,166
[hopeful music playing]

403
00:25:33,250 --> 00:25:34,583
[laughs]

404
00:25:35,625 --> 00:25:37,916
[both laugh]

405
00:25:41,208 --> 00:25:43,125
COURTHOUSE

406
00:25:43,208 --> 00:25:45,208
[indistinct chatter]

407
00:26:03,458 --> 00:26:05,500
[judge] The defendant
has been found guilty.

408
00:26:07,625 --> 00:26:11,458
The sentence.
The defendant is hereby sentenced

409
00:26:11,541 --> 00:26:13,041
to three years in prison.

410
00:26:13,125 --> 00:26:15,791
- [frustrated groans and shouts]
- [upbeat music playing]

411
00:26:16,916 --> 00:26:18,375
[judge] Order in the court.

412
00:26:20,666 --> 00:26:25,125
A hundred and twenty days of time served
shall be credited toward the sentence.

413
00:26:25,916 --> 00:26:29,541
This verdict is due
to the following jurisprudence.

414
00:26:32,708 --> 00:26:33,541
Well done.

415
00:26:33,625 --> 00:26:36,750
I'm surprised you managed to get
only a three-year sentence.

416
00:26:37,666 --> 00:26:41,000
Even so,
Shizuku's problems are far from over.

417
00:26:42,750 --> 00:26:44,208
She may have only gotten three years,

418
00:26:44,291 --> 00:26:46,208
but she'll carry her crime
the rest of her life.

419
00:26:46,708 --> 00:26:49,041
When she gets out,
she could end up being taken advantage of

420
00:26:49,125 --> 00:26:52,708
by someone else like Shuto,
someone who only cares about himself.

421
00:26:54,708 --> 00:26:57,375
Actually, I don't think Shuto
or people like him

422
00:26:57,458 --> 00:26:59,208
care about themselves at all.

423
00:27:02,250 --> 00:27:04,166
This isn't about care or love.

424
00:27:05,750 --> 00:27:09,125
For them, they're just trying desperately
to protect what they have.

425
00:27:11,833 --> 00:27:13,000
I admit…

426
00:27:14,333 --> 00:27:17,000
I wonder if I'm relying
on something unreliable.

427
00:27:18,458 --> 00:27:20,541
Relying on the unreliable…

428
00:27:22,291 --> 00:27:27,500
Everyone's spending their limited
time on earth… worried about status.

429
00:27:28,750 --> 00:27:31,250
But it doesn't matter
how powerful they get.

430
00:27:32,666 --> 00:27:35,666
It's not enough.
So they buy more and more things,

431
00:27:36,208 --> 00:27:39,458
trying desperately to escape
their anxiety and loneliness.

432
00:27:40,833 --> 00:27:43,500
<i>They lose sight of the life</i>
<i>they're meant to live</i>

433
00:27:43,583 --> 00:27:46,666
<i>in exchange for the fleeting</i>
<i>shimmer of consumption,</i>

434
00:27:46,750 --> 00:27:49,416
<i>only to end up feeling</i>
<i>more disconnected than ever.</i>

435
00:27:56,041 --> 00:27:59,541
You are a human rights lawyer, Kujo.
Take my word for it.

436
00:28:00,625 --> 00:28:02,583
No, I don't see it that way.

437
00:28:03,375 --> 00:28:05,375
I'm a lawyer, just a lawyer.

438
00:28:06,416 --> 00:28:07,583
[music fades]

439
00:28:12,083 --> 00:28:15,333
The judgment becomes final
two weeks after it's pronounced.

440
00:28:16,041 --> 00:28:20,166
You won't go to prison right away.
You'll stay here for another month or two.

441
00:28:22,958 --> 00:28:25,208
Three years of incarceration is long.

442
00:28:25,708 --> 00:28:28,750
But remember,
you'll only be 23 when you get out.

443
00:28:33,250 --> 00:28:35,208
[Shizuku] If I get out in three years,

444
00:28:36,416 --> 00:28:37,375
I… I…

445
00:28:38,250 --> 00:28:40,583
What do I do? Where do I go?

446
00:28:40,666 --> 00:28:42,166
[inhales deeply]

447
00:28:43,583 --> 00:28:45,500
I don't belong anywhere.

448
00:28:49,833 --> 00:28:51,541
Take it one day at a time.

449
00:28:52,833 --> 00:28:55,375
If you can cherish the small moments,

450
00:28:56,541 --> 00:28:58,291
that's where you'll find belonging.

451
00:29:00,083 --> 00:29:03,750
No matter where you are,
you can find peace in your heart.

452
00:29:13,250 --> 00:29:14,500
For you…

453
00:29:15,666 --> 00:29:18,541
I'll give my daughter these books
when she's old enough for them.

454
00:29:18,625 --> 00:29:20,583
[mournful choral music playing]

455
00:29:20,666 --> 00:29:22,000
Would you like to have them?

456
00:29:28,083 --> 00:29:30,416
This one's from Mr. Karasuma.

457
00:29:46,125 --> 00:29:48,458
I want you to know,
Shizuku, I'm there for you…

458
00:29:53,166 --> 00:29:55,416
until you're no longer taken advantage of

459
00:29:56,666 --> 00:29:58,750
and instead able to decide for yourself.

460
00:30:01,416 --> 00:30:03,416
[music increases in tempo]

461
00:30:13,416 --> 00:30:15,125
And if you have nowhere to go…

462
00:30:18,541 --> 00:30:20,375
you can always come to my office.

463
00:30:26,041 --> 00:30:27,125
[sniffs]

464
00:30:30,666 --> 00:30:35,000
I think I might understand why
you took on Mr. Kyogoku's case, Mr. Kujo.

465
00:30:36,416 --> 00:30:38,791
Many people who cannot be saved
by the justice system

466
00:30:38,875 --> 00:30:41,041
are victimized by it instead.

467
00:30:41,125 --> 00:30:44,375
You're trying to treat them like humans
in an inhuman system, aren't you?

468
00:30:44,458 --> 00:30:46,791
I doubt if my motives are that noble.

469
00:30:47,458 --> 00:30:50,666
But I'm just trying to do what I can do
with what I have.

470
00:30:50,750 --> 00:30:51,708
[music ends]

471
00:30:55,083 --> 00:30:57,458
Oh, I have to go downstairs. Excuse me.

472
00:30:58,500 --> 00:30:59,833
Sure, no worries.

473
00:31:07,333 --> 00:31:08,250
Mr. Kujo…

474
00:31:12,041 --> 00:31:13,750
What if you lose your license?

475
00:31:15,041 --> 00:31:17,208
If you do, it's all over. For both of us.

476
00:31:18,416 --> 00:31:22,333
If a lawyer can't represent clients,
they can't save anyone anymore.

477
00:31:25,875 --> 00:31:27,416
Mr. Karasuma.

478
00:31:28,708 --> 00:31:29,625
Yes?

479
00:31:30,958 --> 00:31:34,166
Do we need to predict the future
as well as practice law?

480
00:31:34,250 --> 00:31:36,250
[upbeat percussive music playing]

481
00:32:16,166 --> 00:32:18,750
[Tonohata] It's the hotel right there,
room 302.

482
00:32:19,750 --> 00:32:20,583
Uh…

483
00:32:21,625 --> 00:32:25,833
Mr. Suzuki,
the Ultimate Kink Experience, okay?

484
00:32:25,916 --> 00:32:27,375
[call girl sighs] Okay.

485
00:32:27,458 --> 00:32:28,375
Okay.

486
00:32:32,541 --> 00:32:34,666
[man] <i>So, how's it going</i>
<i>driving call girls? Good?</i>

487
00:32:34,750 --> 00:32:35,583
Yeah.

488
00:32:36,208 --> 00:32:38,500
Thanks for introducing me. It's so easy.

489
00:32:39,041 --> 00:32:40,791
Goddammit!

490
00:32:40,875 --> 00:32:45,083
I lost! I bet it all on a long shot!

491
00:32:45,166 --> 00:32:48,458
I was gonna go to a classy brothel
if I won. Fuck!

492
00:32:50,166 --> 00:32:53,250
I lost at cryptocurrency
and FX trading as well.

493
00:32:53,333 --> 00:32:55,416
